<paragraph id="2D02FD0E76344209B9EB29C1FCC694A9" blockId="2.[166,1225,441,780]" box="[166,1225,441,463]" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">
<keyLead id="964C5E3B76344209B9EB29C1FCC694A9" box="[166,1225,441,463]" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">
1. Metapleuron punctate (
<figureCitation id="B586E18B76344209B89929C1FA1194A9" box="[468,542,441,463]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1769,1791]" captionTargetBox="[276,1153,630,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-150@3.[276,1153,630,1748]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Clistopyga, ♀. 1, 3, 5, 7 — metapleuron (lateral view): 1 — C. incitator; 3 — C. rufator; 5 — C. canadensis; 7 — C. sziladyi; 2, 4, 6, 8 — ovipositor (lateral view): 1 — C. incitator; 3 — C. rufator; 5 — C. canadensis; 7 — C. sziladyi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449473" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449473/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">
FIgs 1, 
<emphasis id="1FC9211C76344209BB5E29C1FA1194A9" box="[531,542,441,463]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">1</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="B586E18B76344209BB6429C1FA3B94A9" box="[553,564,441,463]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[174,207,1005,1027]" captionTargetBox="[259,1136,176,991]" captionTargetId="figure-342@5.[259,1136,175,991]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. Polysphincta, ♀. 1–2 — metapleuron (lateral view): 1 — P. tuberosa; 2 — P. vexator; 3–5 — metasoma (dorsal view): 3 — P. tuberosa, tergites III–IV; 4 — P. rufipes, tergites II–IV; 5 — P. vexator, tergites II–IV." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449479" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449479/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">
<emphasis id="1FC9211C76344209BB6429C1FA3B94A9" box="[553,564,441,463]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">3</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Male face yellow or at least with yellow spots (
<figureCitation id="B586E18B76344209BD4D29C1FC3994A9" box="[1024,1078,441,463]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[166,199,1022,1044]" captionTargetBox="[250,1127,175,996]" captionTargetId="figure-223@4.[250,1127,175,997]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Clistopyga, face (frontal view), Ơ: 1 — C. rufator; 2 — C. incitator; 3 — C. canadensis; 4 — C. sziladyi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449475" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449475/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">FIgs 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="B586E18B76344209BD7229C1FC4594A9" box="[1087,1098,441,463]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1769,1791]" captionTargetBox="[276,1153,630,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-150@3.[276,1153,630,1748]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Clistopyga, ♀. 1, 3, 5, 7 — metapleuron (lateral view): 1 — C. incitator; 3 — C. rufator; 5 — C. canadensis; 7 — C. sziladyi; 2, 4, 6, 8 — ovipositor (lateral view): 1 — C. incitator; 3 — C. rufator; 5 — C. canadensis; 7 — C. sziladyi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449473" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449473/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">
<emphasis id="1FC9211C76344209BD7229C1FC4594A9" box="[1087,1098,441,463]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">1</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="B586E18B76344209BD1B29C1FC6E94A9" box="[1110,1121,441,463]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[166,199,1022,1044]" captionTargetBox="[250,1127,175,996]" captionTargetId="figure-223@4.[250,1127,175,997]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Clistopyga, face (frontal view), Ơ: 1 — C. rufator; 2 — C. incitator; 3 — C. canadensis; 4 — C. sziladyi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449475" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449475/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">
<emphasis id="1FC9211C76344209BD1B29C1FC6E94A9" box="[1110,1121,441,463]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">2</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). ............ 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2D02FD0E76344209B9EB29AEFCC6948A" blockId="2.[166,1225,441,780]" box="[166,1225,470,492]" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">
<keyLead id="964C5E3B76344209B9EB29AEFCC6948A" box="[166,1225,470,492]" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">
— Metapleuron smooth or granulate (
<figureCitation id="B586E18B76344209BB0D29AEFA7A948A" box="[576,629,470,492]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1769,1791]" captionTargetBox="[276,1153,630,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-150@3.[276,1153,630,1748]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Clistopyga, ♀. 1, 3, 5, 7 — metapleuron (lateral view): 1 — C. incitator; 3 — C. rufator; 5 — C. canadensis; 7 — C. sziladyi; 2, 4, 6, 8 — ovipositor (lateral view): 1 — C. incitator; 3 — C. rufator; 5 — C. canadensis; 7 — C. sziladyi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449473" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449473/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">FIgs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="1FC9211C76344209BBCD29AEFA84948A" box="[640,651,470,492]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">5</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="1FC9211C76344209BBDB29AEFAAE948A" box="[662,673,470,492]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">7</emphasis>
). Male face black (
<figureCitation id="B586E18B76344209BA1E29AEFB85948A" box="[851,906,470,492]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[166,199,1022,1044]" captionTargetBox="[250,1127,175,996]" captionTargetId="figure-223@4.[250,1127,175,997]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Clistopyga, face (frontal view), Ơ: 1 — C. rufator; 2 — C. incitator; 3 — C. canadensis; 4 — C. sziladyi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449475" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449475/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">FIgs 2</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="1FC9211C76344209BADE29AEFBBA948A" box="[915,949,470,492]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">
<figureCitation id="B586E18B76344209BADE29AEFBAF948A" box="[915,928,470,492]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[174,207,1005,1027]" captionTargetBox="[259,1136,176,991]" captionTargetId="figure-342@5.[259,1136,175,991]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. Polysphincta, ♀. 1–2 — metapleuron (lateral view): 1 — P. tuberosa; 2 — P. vexator; 3–5 — metasoma (dorsal view): 3 — P. tuberosa, tergites III–IV; 4 — P. rufipes, tergites II–IV; 5 — P. vexator, tergites II–IV." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449479" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449479/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="B586E18B76344209BAE729AEFBBA948A" box="[938,949,470,492]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[174,205,1238,1260]" captionTargetBox="[265,1142,174,1221]" captionTargetId="figure-303@7.[265,1142,174,1221]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 4. Schizopyga and Sinarachna, ♀. 1–5 — Schizopyga: 1 — S. coxator, habitus (lateral view); 2 — S. circulator, face (frontal view);3 — S.coxator, face (frontal view);4 — S.coxator, pronotum (lateral view); 5 — S.circulator, pronotum (lateral view); 6–7 — Sinarachna, tergites III–IV of metasoma (dorsal view):6 — S. pallipes; 7 — S. nigricornis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449483" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449483/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">4</figureCitation>
</emphasis>
). ........................................... 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="9649E5AB76344209B9EB298BFCC697FF" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">
<paragraph id="2D02FD0E76344209B9EB298BFCC69724" blockId="2.[166,1225,441,780]" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">
<keyLead id="964C5E3B76344209B9EB298BFCC69724" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">
2. Ovipositor more-or-less uniformly up-curved, the length is about 1.5 × length of hind tibia (
<figureCitation id="B586E18B76344209BD3C298BFCAC976F" box="[1137,1187,499,521]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1769,1791]" captionTargetBox="[276,1153,630,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-150@3.[276,1153,630,1748]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Clistopyga, ♀. 1, 3, 5, 7 — metapleuron (lateral view): 1 — C. incitator; 3 — C. rufator; 5 — C. canadensis; 7 — C. sziladyi; 2, 4, 6, 8 — ovipositor (lateral view): 1 — C. incitator; 3 — C. rufator; 5 — C. canadensis; 7 — C. sziladyi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449473" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449473/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">FIg. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="B586E18B76344209BDE2298BFCB5976F" box="[1199,1210,499,521]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[174,205,1238,1260]" captionTargetBox="[265,1142,174,1221]" captionTargetId="figure-303@7.[265,1142,174,1221]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 4. Schizopyga and Sinarachna, ♀. 1–5 — Schizopyga: 1 — S. coxator, habitus (lateral view); 2 — S. circulator, face (frontal view);3 — S.coxator, face (frontal view);4 — S.coxator, pronotum (lateral view); 5 — S.circulator, pronotum (lateral view); 6–7 — Sinarachna, tergites III–IV of metasoma (dorsal view):6 — S. pallipes; 7 — S. nigricornis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449483" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449483/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">
<emphasis id="1FC9211C76344209BDE2298BFCB5976F" box="[1199,1210,499,521]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">4</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Metapleuron uniformly punctate (
<figureCitation id="B586E18B76344209BB752A68FA679740" box="[568,616,528,550]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1769,1791]" captionTargetBox="[276,1153,630,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-150@3.[276,1153,630,1748]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Clistopyga, ♀. 1, 3, 5, 7 — metapleuron (lateral view): 1 — C. incitator; 3 — C. rufator; 5 — C. canadensis; 7 — C. sziladyi; 2, 4, 6, 8 — ovipositor (lateral view): 1 — C. incitator; 3 — C. rufator; 5 — C. canadensis; 7 — C. sziladyi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449473" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449473/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">FIg. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="B586E18B76344209BB392A68FA709740" box="[628,639,528,550]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[174,207,1005,1027]" captionTargetBox="[259,1136,176,991]" captionTargetId="figure-342@5.[259,1136,175,991]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. Polysphincta, ♀. 1–2 — metapleuron (lateral view): 1 — P. tuberosa; 2 — P. vexator; 3–5 — metasoma (dorsal view): 3 — P. tuberosa, tergites III–IV; 4 — P. rufipes, tergites II–IV; 5 — P. vexator, tergites II–IV." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449479" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449479/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">
<emphasis id="1FC9211C76344209BB392A68FA709740" box="[628,639,528,550]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">3</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Hind coxa and femur without yellow marks. Male face with yellow spots (
<figureCitation id="B586E18B76344209B83C2A54F9AB9724" box="[369,420,556,578]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[166,199,1022,1044]" captionTargetBox="[250,1127,175,996]" captionTargetId="figure-223@4.[250,1127,175,997]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Clistopyga, face (frontal view), Ơ: 1 — C. rufator; 2 — C. incitator; 3 — C. canadensis; 4 — C. sziladyi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449475" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449475/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">FIg. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="B586E18B76344209B8E32A54F9B69724" box="[430,441,556,578]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1769,1791]" captionTargetBox="[276,1153,630,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-150@3.[276,1153,630,1748]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Clistopyga, ♀. 1, 3, 5, 7 — metapleuron (lateral view): 1 — C. incitator; 3 — C. rufator; 5 — C. canadensis; 7 — C. sziladyi; 2, 4, 6, 8 — ovipositor (lateral view): 1 — C. incitator; 3 — C. rufator; 5 — C. canadensis; 7 — C. sziladyi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449473" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449473/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">
<emphasis id="1FC9211C76344209B8E32A54F9B69724" box="[430,441,556,578]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">1</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). ......................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="EABD868D76344209BD212A54FCC69724" authorityName="Holmgren" authorityYear="1856" box="[1132,1225,556,578]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Clistopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufator">
<emphasis id="1FC9211C76344209BD212A54FCC69724" box="[1132,1225,556,578]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">C. rufator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2D02FD0E76344209B9EB2A31FCC697FF" blockId="2.[166,1225,441,780]" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">
<keyLead id="964C5E3B76344209B9EB2A31FCC697FF" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">
— Ovipositor strongly apically up-curved, the length is about 1.8–1.9 × length of hind tibia (
<figureCitation id="B586E18B76344209BD232A31FCAE9739" box="[1134,1185,585,607]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1769,1791]" captionTargetBox="[276,1153,630,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-150@3.[276,1153,630,1748]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Clistopyga, ♀. 1, 3, 5, 7 — metapleuron (lateral view): 1 — C. incitator; 3 — C. rufator; 5 — C. canadensis; 7 — C. sziladyi; 2, 4, 6, 8 — ovipositor (lateral view): 1 — C. incitator; 3 — C. rufator; 5 — C. canadensis; 7 — C. sziladyi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449473" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449473/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">FIg. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="B586E18B76344209BDE22A31FCB59739" box="[1199,1210,585,607]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[166,199,1022,1044]" captionTargetBox="[250,1127,175,996]" captionTargetId="figure-223@4.[250,1127,175,997]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Clistopyga, face (frontal view), Ơ: 1 — C. rufator; 2 — C. incitator; 3 — C. canadensis; 4 — C. sziladyi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449475" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449475/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">
<emphasis id="1FC9211C76344209BDE22A31FCB59739" box="[1199,1210,585,607]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">2</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Metapleuron more densely punctate distally, often impunctate proximally (
<figureCitation id="B586E18B76344209BA9F2A1EFC10971A" box="[978,1055,614,636]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1769,1791]" captionTargetBox="[276,1153,630,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-150@3.[276,1153,630,1748]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Clistopyga, ♀. 1, 3, 5, 7 — metapleuron (lateral view): 1 — C. incitator; 3 — C. rufator; 5 — C. canadensis; 7 — C. sziladyi; 2, 4, 6, 8 — ovipositor (lateral view): 1 — C. incitator; 3 — C. rufator; 5 — C. canadensis; 7 — C. sziladyi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449473" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449473/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">
FIg. 1, 
<emphasis id="1FC9211C76344209BD592A1EFC10971A" box="[1044,1055,614,636]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">1</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). Hind coxa and femur at least partly yellow. Male face entirely yellow (
<figureCitation id="B586E18B76344209BBB92AFBFB3497FF" box="[756,827,643,665]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[166,199,1022,1044]" captionTargetBox="[250,1127,175,996]" captionTargetId="figure-223@4.[250,1127,175,997]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 2. Clistopyga, face (frontal view), Ơ: 1 — C. rufator; 2 — C. incitator; 3 — C. canadensis; 4 — C. sziladyi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449475" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449475/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">
FIg. 2, 
<emphasis id="1FC9211C76344209BA7D2AFBFB3497FF" box="[816,827,643,665]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="369">2</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
). ................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="EABD868D76344209BD122AFBFCC697FF" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1793" box="[1119,1225,643,665]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Clistopyga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incitator">
